modules.description: Manages subscription states by creating and manipulating instances with a given type structure. Operates on polymorphic types wrapped in a module abstraction. Used to initialize and persist subscription configurations in event-driven systems.

Handles WebSocket-based subscription communication by providing message parsing, connection management, and event dispatching. It operates on raw WebSocket frames, JSON-encoded payloads, and event streams. Used to maintain real-time data synchronization in client-server applications with reactive updates.

Manages a collection of named callbacks for event-driven communication, allowing registration, lookup, iteration, and removal of handlers. It operates on a custom type `t` that encapsulates these associations, using strings as keys and functions as values. Used to track and invoke event listeners in a web socket-based subscription system.
